parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation and tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: tires are close to blowing out
tires are rotting and falling apart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities. The starter sticking can also cause the engine to stall, leading to similar consequences.
symptoms: the vehicle loses power and comes to a sudden stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Safety Check Valve in Fuel System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of a safety check valve in the fuel system can cause fuel to continue flowing even when the vehicle is not running, leading to fires, property damage, and potentially injuries or fatalities.
Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, property, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke or flames coming from the engine area

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a complete loss of the vehicle, and may also pose a risk to the safety of occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: flames shooting up from the hood
console or dashboard catching on fire
